Troy Asset Management Ltd Buys Altria Group Inc, Microsoft Corp, American Express Co


May 17, 2017, 11:38:25 AM EDT
By insider, GuruFocus









































Shutterstock photo


Troy Asset Management LtdNew Purchases: MO , MSFT , AXP , DPS, BDX, CL, PG, FNV, FISV, PYPL,For the details of Troy Asset Management Ltd's stock buys and sells, go to http://www.gurufocus.com/StockBuy.php?GuruName=Troy+Asset+Management+LtdThese are the top 5 holdings of Troy Asset Management LtdAltria Group Inc ( MO ) - 3,631,270 shares, 11.94% of the total portfolio. New PositionMicrosoft Corp ( MSFT ) - 3,458,490 shares, 10.55% of the total portfolio. New PositionAmerican Express Co ( AXP ) - 1,531,290 shares, 5.49% of the total portfolio. New PositionDr Pepper Snapple Group Inc ( DPS ) - 1,154,000 shares, 5.09% of the total portfolio. New PositionBecton, Dickinson and Co ( BDX ) - 592,700 shares, 4.77% of the total portfolio. New PositionNew Purchase: Altria Group Inc ( MO )Troy Asset Management Ltd initiated holdings in Altria Group Inc. The purchase prices were between $67.51 and $76.45, with an estimated average price of $72.37. The stock is now traded at around $71.06. The impact to the portfolio due to this purchase was 11.94%. The holdings were 3,631,270 shares as of 2017-03-31.New Purchase: Microsoft Corp ( MSFT )Troy Asset Management Ltd initiated holdings in Microsoft Corp. The purchase prices were between $62.3 and $65.86, with an estimated average price of $64.09. The stock is now traded at around $68.91. The impact to the portfolio due to this purchase was 10.55%. The holdings were 3,458,490 shares as of 2017-03-31.New Purchase: American Express Co ( AXP )Troy Asset Management Ltd initiated holdings in American Express Co. The purchase prices were between $75.32 and $81.92, with an estimated average price of $78.18. The stock is now traded at around $77.14. The impact to the portfolio due to this purchase was 5.49%. The holdings were 1,531,290 shares as of 2017-03-31.New Purchase: Dr Pepper Snapple Group Inc ( DPS )Troy Asset Management Ltd initiated holdings in Dr Pepper Snapple Group Inc. The purchase prices were between $89.49 and $97.92, with an estimated average price of $93.29. The stock is now traded at around $90.42. The impact to the portfolio due to this purchase was 5.09%. The holdings were 1,154,000 shares as of 2017-03-31.New Purchase: Becton, Dickinson and Co ( BDX )Troy Asset Management Ltd initiated holdings in Becton, Dickinson and Co. The purchase prices were between $164.8 and $185.34, with an estimated average price of $178.67. The stock is now traded at around $180.75. The impact to the portfolio due to this purchase was 4.77%. The holdings were 592,700 shares as of 2017-03-31.New Purchase: Colgate-Palmolive Co (CL)Troy Asset Management Ltd initiated holdings in Colgate-Palmolive Co. The purchase prices were between $64.53 and $74.44, with an estimated average price of $70. The stock is now traded at around $73.86. The impact to the portfolio due to this purchase was 4.58%. The holdings were 1,435,400 shares as of 2017-03-31.MO 15-Year Financial DataThe intrinsic value of MOPeter Lynch Chart of MOPremium MembersThis article first appeared on GuruFocus .



