Personal Assets Trust
							Troy Income and Growth Trust
							


















Investment Trusts









We were appointed investment adviser to Personal Assets Trust plc in 2009. The Company was listed in 1983 and it is a constituent of the FTSE 250 Index.
In 2009, Troy was appointed investment manager of the Troy Income & Growth Trust plc. It was founded in 1988 and was formerly known as Glasgow Income Trust plc. For both these investment trusts we aim to protect and grow investors’ capital whilst delivering lower than average volatility through the investment cycle.
 

 





Personal Assets Trust

 



 

Personal Assets Trust is a portfolio that invests in multiple asset classes and geographies in a similar way to the Trojan Fund. It has a large investor base among private individuals and its primary objective is to protect their wealth in real terms over the long-term. Its secondary objective is to provide capital growth.
 
Find out more
http://www.patplc.co.uk/

 





Troy Income & Growth Trust

 



 

Troy Income & Growth Trust aims to generate an attractive income yield predominantly by investing in UK-listed companies which exhibit potential growth in income and capital. The trust is invested in a similar way to the Trojan Income Fund.
 
Find out more
http://www.tigt.co.uk/

 













 

