Our History









Our History










Troy Asset Management was established in 2000 by the late Lord Weinstock. The company is named after his 1979 Epsom Derby winner.
The company remains an independent boutique. Fund managers are shareholders in Troy and Funds managed by Troy. 
Our Timeline



2000

Sebastian Lyon establishes Troy Asset Management


2001

Trojan Fund is launched


2004

Francis Brooke joins Troy Asset Management to launch the Trojan Income Fund



2006

Trojan Capital Fund is launched


2008

Spectrum Fund is launched


2009

Troy appointed Investment Adviser to Personal Assets Trust


2009

Troy appointed Investment Manager of Troy Income & Growth Trust


2011

Gabrielle Boyle joins Troy and is appointed Fund Manager of the Trojan Capital Fund


2014

Tom Yeowart joins Troy and is appointed Fund Manager of the Spectrum Fund


2015

Trojan Capital Fund renamed Trojan Global Equity Fund


2015

Troy appointed Investment Manager of the Electric & General Investment Fund


2016

Trojan Ethical Income Fund is launched


2016

James Harries joins Troy to launch the Trojan Global Income Fund




 














 

